                            <comment id="98071" author="adilger" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 17:34:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this was fixed for b2_5 via &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4811&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.5&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;2.6 failure on test suite sanity test_24u: error on ioctl 0x4008669a, no data availiable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  The &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/9812&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/9812&lt;/a&gt; patch would need to be backported to b2_4 to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="97751" author="adilger" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2014 20:24:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking more closely at the test configurations, it appears that this is being hit on &quot;full&quot; runs when using a 2.4 MDS.  Some kind of interop problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
